	0707a        d590f6      CMP0            !0F690H
	0707d        dd06        BZ              $7085H // if state is 0, set to param A
	0707f        4090f607    CMP             !0F690H,#7H // if state is 7

:sub_7SEG_ClearMem_9b74
	09b74        f446        CLRB            0FFE46H
	09b76        f447        CLRB            0FFE47H
	09b78        f448        CLRB            0FFE48H
	09b7a        f449        CLRB            0FFE49H

	09b7f        f44a        CLRB            0FFE4AH
	09b81        f44b        CLRB            0FFE4BH
	09b83        d7          RET    

// Very similar to function just below
// TOP 30
// Called 31 times
// A is either 1 or 2
// 
:sub_7Seg_WriteSegment_9b84
	09b84        c3          PUSH            BC
	09b85        70          MOV             X,A //a=1,x=1
	09b86        63          MOV             A,B //a=65,x=1
	09b87        5c80        AND             A,#80H // a=0
	09b89        72          MOV             C,A //a=0,c=0,x=1
	09b8a        63          MOV             A,B //a=65,c=0,x=1
	09b8b        5c7f        AND             A,#7FH // a=65
	09b8d        73          MOV             B,A // a=65,b=65,c=0,x=1
	09b8e        094211      MOV             A,1142H[B] // get index into mem
	//1142 
	// 3f065b4f666d7d07 - long string
	09b91        616a        OR              A,C // if top bit was set, set it again
	09b93        7cff        XOR             A,#0FFH // FF-result
	09b95        08          XCH             A,X
	09b96        4c01        CMP             A,#1H // is original A = 1
	09b98        60          MOV             A,X // A back to result
	09b99        df05        BNZ             $9BA0H
	09b9b        9f46f6      MOV             !0F646H,A // where to store
	09b9e        ef03        BR              $9BA3H
	09ba0        9f47f6      MOV             !0F647H,A
	09ba3        fc749b00    CALL            !!9B74H
	09ba7        c2          POP             BC
	09ba8        d7          RET             

// TOP 15
// At init a = 16, b = 16
// a = 65, b=6c common
:sub_7Seg_Write_v2_9ba9

09bac        72          MOV             C,A // A=6c,b=65,c=6c
09bad        e1          ONEB            A   //	a=1,b=65,c=6c
09bae        fc849b00    CALL            sub_7Seg_WriteSegment_9b84
09bb2        62          MOV             A,C //
09bb3        73          MOV             B,A
09bb4        5102        MOV             A,#2H
09bb6        fc849b00    CALL            sub_7Seg_WriteSegment_9b84
09bba        e44a        ONEB            0FFE4AH
09bbc        c2          POP             BC
09bbd        d7          RET

:sub_Serial_WriteHexAsDec_e204

:sub_Serial_WriteStringAT_UART1_e322

// Send whatever is in AX to EEPROM
:sub_EEPROM_Send_e388      
	0e388        c3          PUSH            BC
	0e389        fdc404      CALL            !4C4H
	0e38c        02bd20      ADDW            AX,!20BDH
	0e38f        5010        MOV             X,#10H
	0e391        ef09        BR              $0E39CH
	0e393        da20        MOVW            BC,0FFE20H
	0e395        311c        SHLW            BC,1H
	0e397        33          XCHW            AX,BC
	0e398        bd20        MOVW            0FFE20H,AX
	0e39a        13          MOVW            AX,BC
	0e39b        90          DEC             X
	0e39c        317421f3    BF              0FFE21H.7H,$0E393H
	0e3a0        60          MOV             A,X
	0e3a1        90          DEC             X
	0e3a2        d1          CMP0            A
	0e3a3        dd1c        BZ              $0E3C1H
	0e3a5        71230e      CLR1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e3a8        31742105    BF              0FFE21H.7H,$0E3B1H
	// Clocking data out
	0e3ac        71120b      SET1            EEPROM_DI
	0e3af        ef03        BR              $0E3B4H
	0e3b1        71130b      CLR1            EEPROM_DI
	0e3b4        71220e      SET1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e3b7        da20        MOVW            BC,0FFE20H
	0e3b9        311c        SHLW            BC,1H
	0e3bb        33          XCHW            AX,BC
	0e3bc        bd20        MOVW            0FFE20H,AX
	0e3be        13          MOVW            AX,BC
	0e3bf        efdf        BR              $0E3A0H
	0e3c1        fd0b05      CALL            !50BH
	0e3c4        02c2d7      ADDW            AX,!0D7C2H
// end sub_EEPROM_Send_e388

// setup DI and CS 
// assert CS for correct chip based on F65B
:sub_EEPROM_Init_e3c7
	0e3c7        8efa        MOV             A,PSW
	0e3c9        9803        MOV             [SP+3H],A
	0e3cb        717bfa      DI              
	0e3ce        71130b      CLR1            EEPROM_DI
	0e3d1        71130e      CLR1            EEPROM_CS_IC8
	0e3d4        71530e      CLR1            EEPROM_CS_IC11
	0e3d7        71220e      SET1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e3da        00          NOP             
	0e3db        71230e      CLR1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e3de        71130b      CLR1            EEPROM_DI
	0e3e1        d55bf6      CMP0            !0F65BH
	0e3e4        dd05        BZ              $0E3EBH
	0e3e6        71520e      SET1            EEPROM_CS_IC11
	0e3e9        61ec        RETB            
	0e3eb        71120e      SET1            EEPROM_CS_IC8
	0e3ee        61ec        RETB       
// end sub_EEPROM_Init_e3c7

// Takes EEPROM address in AX
// Returns 16bit value in 0xE046
:sub_EEPROM_Read_e3f0     
	0e3f0        77          MOV             H,A
	0e3f1        8efa        MOV             A,PSW
	0e3f3        9803        MOV             [SP+3H],A
	0e3f5        67          MOV             A,H
	0e3f6        717bfa      DI              					// Disable interrupts
	0e3f9        c3          PUSH            BC
	0e3fa        c5          PUSH            DE
	0e3fb        14          MOVW            DE,AX
	0e3fc        448813      CMPW            AX,#1388H			// Is AX < 5000?
	0e3ff        dc09        BC              $0E40AH
	0e401        0478ec      ADDW            AX,#0EC78H
	0e404        14          MOVW            DE,AX
	0e405        e55bf6      ONEB            !0F65BH
	0e408        ef03        BR              $0E40DH
	0e40a        f55bf6      CLRB            !0F65BH
	0e40d        fcc7e300    CALL            sub_EEPROM_Init_e3c7 // Call with F65B set if >5k
	0e411        15          MOVW            AX,DE
	0e412        311e        SHRW            AX,1H
	// This ends up with 0b0001 10xx xxxx xxxx in AX, where x is address passed
	// 0b110 is read command
	0e414        6c18        OR              A,#18H
	0e416        fc88e300    CALL            sub_EEPROM_Send_e388
	0e41a        71230e      CLR1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e41d        71120b      SET1            EEPROM_DI
	0e420        71220e      SET1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e423        f7          CLRW            BC
	0e424        5500        MOV             D,#0H
	0e426        ef13        BR              $0E43BH
	0e428        311c        SHLW            BC,1H
	0e42a        71230e      CLR1            EEPROM_CLK			// CLK down
	0e42d        31040206    BF              EEPROM_DO,$0E437H	// Test value of DO
	0e431        13          MOVW            AX,BC
	0e432        08          XCH             A,X
	0e433        6c01        OR              A,#1H
	0e435        08          XCH             A,X
	0e436        12          MOVW            BC,AX
	0e437        71220e      SET1            EEPROM_CLK			// CLK up
	0e43a        85          INC             D
	0e43b        65          MOV             A,D
	0e43c        4c10        CMP             A,#10H 			// 16 bits shift in
	0e43e        dce8        BC              $0E428H
	0e440        71230e      CLR1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e443        71130e      CLR1            EEPROM_CS_IC8
	0e446        71530e      CLR1            EEPROM_CS_IC11
	0e449        13          MOVW            AX,BC
	0e44a        bf46e0      MOVW            !0E046H,AX 		// Copy value to E046
	0e44d        c4          POP             DE
	0e44e        c2          POP             BC
	0e44f        61ec        RETB       
// end sub_EEPROM_Read_e3f0 

:sub_EEPROM_Write_e451
	0e451        77          MOV             H,A
	0e452        8efa        MOV             A,PSW
	0e454        9803        MOV             [SP+3H],A
	0e456        67          MOV             A,H
	0e457        717bfa      DI              
	0e45a        c5          PUSH            DE
	0e45b        fdc404      CALL            !4C4H
	0e45e        02
	0e45f		 33 		 XCHW            AX,BC
	0e460        bd20        MOVW            0FFE20H,AX
	0e462        13          MOVW            AX,BC
	0e463        14          MOVW            DE,AX
	0e464        fcf0e300    CALL            sub_EEPROM_Read_e3f0 // Checks to see if value same
	0e468        fa20        MOVW            HL,0FFE20H
	0e46a        af46e0      MOVW            AX,!0E046H
	0e46d        47          CMPW            AX,HL
	0e46e        61f8        SKNZ            
		0e470        eec700      BR              $!0E53AH // return without writing
	0e473        71423c      SET1            0FFE3CH.4H // Set this if we acutally write
	0e476        15          MOVW            AX,DE
	0e477        448813      CMPW            AX,#1388H // which chip?
	0e47a        dc09        BC              $0E485H
	0e47c        0478ec      ADDW            AX,#0EC78H
	0e47f        14          MOVW            DE,AX
	0e480        e55bf6      ONEB            !0F65BH
	0e483        ef03        BR              $0E488H
	0e485        f55bf6      CLRB            !0F65BH
	0e488        15          MOVW            AX,DE
	0e489        311e        SHRW            AX,1H
	0e48b        14          MOVW            DE,AX
	0e48c        fcc7e300    CALL            sub_EEPROM_Init_e3c7
	0e490        ef04        BR              $0E496H
	// This looks like it could get stuck
	0e492        f6          CLRW            AX
	0e493        bfaaf5      MOVW            !0F5AAH,AX
	0e496        af48e0      MOVW            AX,!0E048H
	0e499        4455aa      CMPW            AX,#0AA55H
	0e49c        dff4        BNZ             $0E492H
	// 0b10011 = EWEN command (erase/write enable)
	0e49e        300013      MOVW            AX,#1300H
	0e4a1        fc88e300    CALL            sub_EEPROM_Send_e388
	0e4a5        71230e      CLR1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e4a8        fcc7e300    CALL            sub_EEPROM_Init_e3c7
	0e4ac        15          MOVW            AX,DE
	// 0b10100 = WRITE command
	0e4ad        6c14        OR              A,#14H
	0e4af        fc88e300    CALL            sub_EEPROM_Send_e388
	0e4b3        f0          CLRB            X
	0e4b4        ef0f        BR              $0E4C5H
	0e4b6        71130b      CLR1            EEPROM_DI
	0e4b9        71220e      SET1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e4bc        da20        MOVW            BC,0FFE20H
	0e4be        311c        SHLW            BC,1H
	0e4c0        33          XCHW            AX,BC
	0e4c1        bd20        MOVW            0FFE20H,AX
	0e4c3        13          MOVW            AX,BC
	0e4c4        80          INC             X
	0e4c5        60          MOV             A,X
	0e4c6        4c10        CMP             A,#10H
	0e4c8        de0c        BNC             $0E4D6H
	0e4ca        71230e      CLR1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e4cd        317421e5    BF              0FFE21H.7H,$0E4B6H
	0e4d1        71120b      SET1            EEPROM_DI
	0e4d4        efe3        BR              $0E4B9H
	0e4d6        71230e      CLR1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e4d9        71130e      CLR1            EEPROM_CS_IC8
	0e4dc        71530e      CLR1            EEPROM_CS_IC11
	0e4df        71220e      SET1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e4e2        00          NOP             
	0e4e3        71230e      CLR1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e4e6        71120b      SET1            EEPROM_DI
	0e4e9        d55bf6      CMP0            !0F65BH
	0e4ec        dd05        BZ              $0E4F3H
	0e4ee        71520e      SET1            EEPROM_CS_IC11
	0e4f1        ef03        BR              $0E4F6H
	0e4f3        71120e      SET1            EEPROM_CS_IC8
	0e4f6        71220e      SET1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e4f9        f0          CLRB            X
	0e4fa        ef08        BR              $0E504H
	0e4fc        71230e      CLR1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e4ff        00          NOP             
	0e500        71220e      SET1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e503        00          NOP             
	0e504        60          MOV             A,X
	0e505        80          INC             X
	0e506        4c0a        CMP             A,#0AH
	0e508        61d8        SKNC            
	0e50a        310202ee    BT              EEPROM_DO,$0E4FCH
	0e50e        3102020a    BT              EEPROM_DO,$0E51CH
	0e512        71230e      CLR1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e515        00          NOP             
	0e516        71220e      SET1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e519        00          NOP             
	0e51a        eff2        BR              $0E50EH
	0e51c        71230e      CLR1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e51f        fcc7e300    CALL            sub_EEPROM_Init_e3c7
	// EWDS - Erase/Write Disable
	0e523        300010      MOVW            AX,#1000H
	0e526        fc88e300    CALL            sub_EEPROM_Send_e388
	0e52a        71230e      CLR1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e52d        71130e      CLR1            EEPROM_CS_IC8
	0e530        71530e      CLR1            EEPROM_CS_IC11
	0e533        71220e      SET1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e536        00          NOP             
	0e537        71230e      CLR1            EEPROM_CLK
	0e53a        fd0b05      CALL            !50BH
	0e53d        02c461      ADDW            AX,!61C4H
	0e540 		 ec

// Incorrect dis
//0e540        ecc1b800    BR              !!0B8C1H

// Returns the byte pointed to by the memory address in AX in A
:sub_EEPROM_ReadByte_e541
	0e541 		 c1 		 PUSH			 AX
	0e542 		 b800 		 MOVW 			 [SP+0H],AX
	0e544        a800        MOVW            AX,[SP+0H]
	0e546        fcf0e300    CALL            sub_EEPROM_Read_e3f0
	0e54a        fbf8ff      MOVW            HL,SP
	0e54d        318505      BF              [HL].0H,$0E555H
	0e550        8f47e0      MOV             A,!0E047H
	0e553        ef03        BR              $0E558H
	0e555        8f46e0      MOV             A,!0E046H
	0e558        1002        ADDW            SP,#2H
	0e55a        d7          RET 

// Returns the word pointed to by AX in AX
:sub_EEPROM_ReadReturnReg_e55b
	0e55b        fcf0e300    CALL            sub_EEPROM_Read_e3f0
	0e55f        af46e0      MOVW            AX,!0E046H
	0e562        d7          RET             

// Reads a byte from EEPROM as DEC converts to HEX
// i.e. 0x34 -> 0x22 (34)
// TOP 17
:sub_EEPROM_ReadByteDecAsHex_e563
	0e563        c3          PUSH            BC
	0e564        fc41e500    CALL            sub_EEPROM_ReadByte_e541
	0e568        73          MOV             B,A
	0e569        5c0f        AND             A,#0FH
	0e56b        72          MOV             C,A
	0e56c        500a        MOV             X,#0AH
	0e56e        63          MOV             A,B
	0e56f        314a        SHR             A,4H
	0e571        d6          MULU            X
	0e572        60          MOV             A,X
	0e573        610a        ADD             A,C
	0e575        c2          POP             BC
	0e576        d7          RET    

// Reads two bytes from EEPROM, converts 0x9378 -> 0x24A2
// Address in AX, returns in AX
:sub_EEPROM_ReadDecAsHex_e577
	0e577        c3          PUSH            BC
	0e578        c5          PUSH            DE
	0e579        fcf0e300    CALL            sub_EEPROM_Read_e3f0
	0e57d        8f46e0      MOV             A,!0E046H
	0e580        f0          CLRB            X
	0e581        5c0f        AND             A,#0FH
	0e583        08          XCH             A,X
	0e584        16          MOVW            HL,AX
	0e585        8f46e0      MOV             A,!0E046H
	0e588        314a        SHR             A,4H
	0e58a        70          MOV             X,A
	0e58b        f1          CLRB            A
	0e58c        320a00      MOVW            BC,#0AH
	0e58f        fd1602      CALL            sub_Multiply_216
	0e592        07          ADDW            AX,HL
	0e593        14          MOVW            DE,AX
	0e594        8f47e0      MOV             A,!0E047H
	0e597        f0          CLRB            X
	0e598        5c0f        AND             A,#0FH
	0e59a        08          XCH             A,X
	0e59b        5264        MOV             C,#64H
	0e59d        fd1602      CALL            sub_Multiply_216
	0e5a0        16          MOVW            HL,AX
	0e5a1        8f47e0      MOV             A,!0E047H
	0e5a4        314a        SHR             A,4H
	0e5a6        70          MOV             X,A
	0e5a7        f1          CLRB            A
	0e5a8        32e803      MOVW            BC,#3E8H
	0e5ab        fd1602      CALL            sub_Multiply_216
	0e5ae        07          ADDW            AX,HL
	0e5af        05          ADDW            AX,DE
	0e5b0        c4          POP             DE
	0e5b1        c2          POP             BC
	0e5b2        d7          RET           

// AX is address
// BC is destination memory address
// D is length
:sub_EEPROM_ReadString_e5b3
	0e5b3        fdc404      CALL            !4C4H
	0e5b6        04bd20      ADDW            AX,#20BDH
	0e5b9        13          MOVW            AX,BC
	0e5ba        bd22        MOVW            0FFE22H,AX
	0e5bc        ad20        MOVW            AX,0FFE20H
	0e5be        fcf0e300    CALL            sub_EEPROM_Read_e3f0
	0e5c2        ef16        BR              $0E5DAH
	0e5c4        8f47e0      MOV             A,!0E047H
	0e5c7        fa22        MOVW            HL,0FFE22H
	0e5c9        9b          MOV             [HL],A
	0e5ca        ad22        MOVW            AX,0FFE22H
	0e5cc        a1          INCW            AX
	0e5cd        bd22        MOVW            0FFE22H,AX
	0e5cf        ad20        MOVW            AX,0FFE20H
	0e5d1        a1          INCW            AX
	0e5d2        bd20        MOVW            0FFE20H,AX
	0e5d4        ad20        MOVW            AX,0FFE20H
	0e5d6        fcf0e300    CALL            sub_EEPROM_Read_e3f0
	0e5da        65          MOV             A,D
	0e5db        95          DEC             D
	0e5dc        d1          CMP0            A
	0e5dd        dd16        BZ              $0E5F5H
	0e5df        310220e1    BT              0FFE20H.0H,$0E5C4H
	0e5e3        ad20        MOVW            AX,0FFE20H
	0e5e5        a1          INCW            AX
	0e5e6        bd20        MOVW            0FFE20H,AX
	0e5e8        8f46e0      MOV             A,!0E046H
	0e5eb        fa22        MOVW            HL,0FFE22H
	0e5ed        9b          MOV             [HL],A
	0e5ee        ad22        MOVW            AX,0FFE22H
	0e5f0        a1          INCW            AX
	0e5f1        bd22        MOVW            0FFE22H,AX
	0e5f3        efe5        BR              $0E5DAH
	0e5f5        ad22        MOVW            AX,0FFE22H
	0e5f7        fd0b05      CALL            !50BH
	0e5fa        04d7
//0e5fa        04d7fd      ADDW            AX,#0FDD7H

:sub_EEPROM_ReadHexAsAscci_0e5fc		
	0e5fc        fdc404      CALL            !4C4H
	0e5ff        04
	0e600 		 bd20      	 MOVW            0FFE20H,AX
	0e602        13       	 MOVW            AX,BC
	0e603        bd22        MOVW            0FFE22H,AX
	0e605        ef2e        BR              $0E635H
	0e607        ad20        MOVW            AX,0FFE20H
	0e609        fc41e500    CALL            sub_EEPROM_ReadByte_e541
	0e60d        73          MOV             B,A
	0e60e        ad20        MOVW            AX,0FFE20H
	0e610        a1          INCW            AX
	0e611        bd20        MOVW            0FFE20H,AX
	0e613        63          MOV             A,B
	0e614        314a        SHR             A,4H
	0e616        fcd63901    CALL            sub_HexToAscii_139d6
	0e61a        fa22        MOVW            HL,0FFE22H
	0e61c        9b          MOV             [HL],A
	0e61d        ad22        MOVW            AX,0FFE22H
	0e61f        a1          INCW            AX
	0e620        bd22        MOVW            0FFE22H,AX
	0e622        63          MOV             A,B
	0e623        5c0f        AND             A,#0FH
	0e625        fcd63901    CALL            sub_HexToAscii_139d6
	0e629        fa22        MOVW            HL,0FFE22H
	0e62b        9b          MOV             [HL],A
	0e62c        ad22        MOVW            AX,0FFE22H
	0e62e        a1          INCW            AX
	0e62f        bd22        MOVW            0FFE22H,AX
	0e631        65          MOV             A,D
	0e632        0cfe        ADD             A,#0FEH
	0e634        75          MOV             D,A
	0e635        65          MOV             A,D
	0e636        7c80        XOR             A,#80H
	0e638        2c81        SUB             A,#81H
	0e63a        decb        BNC             $0E607H
	0e63c        ad22        MOVW            AX,0FFE22H
	0e63e        fd0b05      CALL            !50BH

// Bad dis
//0e641        04d7fd      ADDW            AX,#0FDD7H
//0e644        c4          POP             DE
//0e645        0404bd      ADDW            AX,#0BD04H
//0e648        2013        SUBW            SP,#13H

// Called from ICCID area
// AX = 0x130
// BC = 0xE17E
// D = 0x14

// AX = EEPROM address
// BC = Destination
// D = length
:sub_EEPROM_ReadHexAsAscci_0e643
	0e643        fdc404      CALL 			 !4C4H
	0e466 		 04 // This is a parameter to the above function
	0e467 		 bd20     	 MOVW            0FFE20H,AX // Move out EEPROM address
	0e649 		 13       	 MOVW            AX,BC
	0e64a        bd22        MOVW            0FFE22H,AX // Move address of return into 0xFFE22
	0e64c        ef3c        BR              $0E68AH
	0e64e        ad20        MOVW            AX,0FFE20H // EEPROM address back into AX
	0e650        fc41e500    CALL            sub_EEPROM_ReadByte_e541
	0e654        73          MOV             B,A
	0e655        ad20        MOVW            AX,0FFE20H // increment EEPROM address
	0e657        a1          INCW            AX
	0e658        bd20        MOVW            0FFE20H,AX
	0e65a        63          MOV             A,B
	0e65b        5cf0        AND             A,#0F0H // Get top digit
	0e65d        4ce0        CMP             A,#0E0H // 
	0e65f        dd0f        BZ              $0E670H
		0e661        63          MOV             A,B
		0e662        314a        SHR             A,4H
		0e664        fcd63901    CALL            sub_HexToAscii_139d6
		0e668        fa22        MOVW            HL,0FFE22H // Appears to be address of a buffer
		0e66a        9b          MOV             [HL],A     // Store ASCII in buffer
		0e66b        ad22        MOVW            AX,0FFE22H
		0e66d        a1          INCW            AX
		0e66e        bd22        MOVW            0FFE22H,AX // increment address
	0e670        63          MOV             A,B
	0e671        5c0f        AND             A,#0FH // get bottom digit
	0e673        4c0e        CMP             A,#0EH
	0e675        dd0f        BZ              $0E686H
		0e677        63          MOV             A,B
		0e678        5c0f        AND             A,#0FH
		0e67a        fcd63901    CALL            sub_HexToAscii_139d6
		0e67e        fa22        MOVW            HL,0FFE22H
		0e680        9b          MOV             [HL],A
		0e681        ad22        MOVW            AX,0FFE22H
		0e683        a1          INCW            AX
		0e684        bd22        MOVW            0FFE22H,AX
	0e686        65          MOV             A,D
	0e687        0cfe        ADD             A,#0FEH
	0e689        75          MOV             D,A
	0e68a        65          MOV             A,D
	0e68b        7c80        XOR             A,#80H
	0e68d        2c81        SUB             A,#81H
	0e68f        debd        BNC             $0E64EH // A horrible check for length
	0e691        ad22        MOVW            AX,0FFE22H
	0e693        fd0b05      CALL            !50BH
// This seems to be end of functions

// Bad dis
//0e696        04d7fd      ADDW            AX,#0FDD7H
//0e699        c4          POP             DE
//0e69a        0404bd      ADDW            AX,#0BD04H
//0e69d        2013        SUBW            SP,#13H

// TOP 24
// BC e13e e20e
// AX small - looks like address
// D 10, 14
:sub_EEPROM_CopyToRam_e698
	0e698        fdc404		 CALL 			 !4C4H
	0e69b 		 04
	0e69c 		 bd20 		 MOVW            0FFE20H,AX
	0e69e        13       	 MOVW            AX,BC
	0e69f        bd22        MOVW            0FFE22H,AX
	0e6a1        65          MOV             A,D
	0e6a2        311a        SHR             A,1H
	0e6a4        75          MOV             D,A
	0e6a5        ef10        BR              $0E6B7H
	0e6a7        8f47e0      MOV             A,!0E047H
	0e6aa        fa22        MOVW            HL,0FFE22H
	0e6ac        9b          MOV             [HL],A // store other half of data
	0e6ad        fa22        MOVW            HL,0FFE22H
	0e6af        a7          INCW            HL
	0e6b0        37          XCHW            AX,HL
	0e6b1        bd22        MOVW            0FFE22H,AX
	0e6b3        17          MOVW            AX,HL
	0e6b4        d1          CMP0            A
	0e6b5        dd21        BZ              $0E6D8H
	0e6b7        65          MOV             A,D
	0e6b8        95          DEC             D // looks like D is a length
	0e6b9        d1          CMP0            A
	0e6ba        dd21        BZ              $0E6DDH // when 0 jump to end
	0e6bc        ad20        MOVW            AX,0FFE20H
	0e6be        fcf0e300    CALL            sub_EEPROM_Read_e3f0
	0e6c2        ad20        MOVW            AX,0FFE20H
	0e6c4        a1          INCW            AX
	0e6c5        a1          INCW            AX // bump address by 2
	0e6c6        bd20        MOVW            0FFE20H,AX
	0e6c8        8f46e0      MOV             A,!0E046H // result is here
	0e6cb        fa22        MOVW            HL,0FFE22H // this was BC
	0e6cd        9b          MOV             [HL],A // store data
	0e6ce        fa22        MOVW            HL,0FFE22H
	0e6d0        a7          INCW            HL 		// increment addres
	0e6d1        37          XCHW            AX,HL
	0e6d2        bd22        MOVW            0FFE22H,AX // store back
	0e6d4        17          MOVW            AX,HL
	0e6d5        d1          CMP0            A // is data - check for null
	0e6d6        dfcf        BNZ             $0E6A7H
	0e6d8        ad22        MOVW            AX,0FFE22H
	0e6da        b1          DECW            AX
	0e6db        bd22        MOVW            0FFE22H,AX
	// return
	0e6dd        fa22        MOVW            HL,0FFE22H
	0e6df        f1          CLRB            A
	0e6e0        9b          MOV             [HL],A // null terminate string
	0e6e1        ad22        MOVW            AX,0FFE22H
	0e6e3        fd0b05      CALL            !50BH
// Bad dis
//0e6e6        04d736      ADDW            AX,#36D7H
//0e6e9        55aa        MOV             D,#0AAH

// TOP 13
// Think you need to write AA55 to e048 to allow a write
:sub_EEPROM_WriteGuard_e6e8
	0e6e8 		 3655aa	 	 MOVW			 HL,#0AA55H
	0e6eb        37          XCHW            AX,HL
	0e6ec        bf48e0      MOVW            !0E048H,AX
	0e6ef        17          MOVW            AX,HL
	0e6f0        fc51e400    CALL            sub_EEPROM_Write_e451
	0e6f4        f6          CLRW            AX
	0e6f5        bf48e0      MOVW            !0E048H,AX
	0e6f8        d7          RET           

// TOP 11  
:sub_EEPROM_WriteGuard_e6f9
	0e6f9        3655aa      MOVW            HL,#0AA55H
	0e6fc        37          XCHW            AX,HL
	0e6fd        bf48e0      MOVW            !0E048H,AX
	0e700        17          MOVW            AX,HL
	0e701        71433c      CLR1            0FFE3CH.4H // Flag used to say writing occured
	0e704        fc51e400    CALL            sub_EEPROM_Write_e451
	0e708        31443c09    BF              0FFE3CH.4H,$0E715H
	0e70c        f7          CLRW            BC
	0e70d        b3          DECW            BC
	0e70e        30fe07      MOVW            AX,#7FEH // 2046
	0e711        fc51e400    CALL            sub_EEPROM_Write_e451
	0e715        f6          CLRW            AX
	0e716        bf48e0      MOVW            !0E048H,AX
	0e719        d7          RET          

// TOP 21
// Read from EEPROM address
// Write back
	0e71a        c3          PUSH            BC // Data?
	0e71b        c1          PUSH            AX // Address
	0e71c        b800        MOVW            [SP+0H],AX
	0e71e        a800        MOVW            AX,[SP+0H]
	0e720        fcf0e300    CALL            sub_EEPROM_Read_e3f0 // returns in e046
	0e724        fbf8ff      MOVW            HL,SP
	0e727        63          MOV             A,B
	0e728        318505      BF              [HL].0H,$0E730H // if bottom bit AX set, put in 46, otherwise 47
		0e72b        9f47e0      MOV             !0E047H,A
		0e72e        ef03        BR              $0E733H
	0e730        9f46e0      MOV             !0E046H,A
	0e733        db46e0      MOVW            BC,!0E046H
	0e736        a800        MOVW            AX,[SP+0H]
	0e738        fcf9e600    CALL            sub_EEPROM_WriteGuard_e6f9
	0e73c        1002        ADDW            SP,#2H
	0e73e        c2          POP             BC
	0e73f        d7          RET             

	0e740        fdc404      CALL            !4C4H
	0e743        04bd20      ADDW            AX,#20BDH
	0e746        13          MOVW            AX,BC
	0e747        bd22        MOVW            0FFE22H,AX
	0e749        ef11        BR              $0E75CH
	0e74b        53ee        MOV             B,#0EEH
	0e74d        ad20        MOVW            AX,0FFE20H
	0e74f        fc1ae700    CALL            !!0E71AH

// A is either 4 or 5     
// Seems to be address table at 1f36-1f56
// 1f46 is minimum due to A being 4/5
// 1f46 -> 1f8a -> 35 -> 5
// 1f4A -> 1f56 -> 31 -> 1   
// Seems to be text like FAIL, WAIT, FINISH
// Only ever called and then sent to UART3
	10959        c3          PUSH            BC
	1095a        70          MOV             X,A // x = 4/5
	1095b        8fadf7      MOV             A,!0F7ADH
	1095e        72          MOV             C,A // C = mem
	1095f        f3          CLRB            B 
	10960        311c        SHLW            BC,1H // shift mem right 1
	10962        f1          CLRB            A
	10963        312d        SHLW            AX,2H // shift 4/5 right 2 4->0x10 5->0x14
	10965        04361f      ADDW            AX,#1F36H // add 1f36
	10968        03          ADDW            AX,BC // add mem + result
	10969        16          MOVW            HL,AX // into HL
	1096a        ab          MOVW            AX,[HL] // get memory
	1096b        c2          POP             BC
	1096c        d7          RET

// TOP 23
// Buzzer
:sub_Buzzer_12e31
	12e31        c3          PUSH            BC
	12e32        44f401      CMPW            AX,#1F4H
	12e35        61d8        SKNC            
	12e37        30f401      MOVW            AX,#1F4H
	12e3a        448913      CMPW            AX,#1389H
	12e3d        61c8        SKC             
	12e3f        308813      MOVW            AX,#1388H // 5000
	12e42        360000      MOVW            HL,#0H
	12e45        37          XCHW            AX,HL
	12e46        bf9201      MOVW            !TMR01,AX // timer mode register
	12e49        17          MOVW            AX,HL
	12e4a        36ba01      MOVW            HL,#1BAH // timer output enable reg
	12e4d        7193        CLR1            [HL].1H
	12e4f        326400      MOVW            BC,#64H
	12e52        fd3102      CALL            sub_DivideResultZero_231 // Divide AX by BC
	12e55        12          MOVW            BC,AX
	12e56        30a861      MOVW            AX,#61A8H // 25000
	12e59        fd3102      CALL            sub_DivideResultZero_231
	12e5c        bd1a        MOVW            TDR01,AX // Timer data register
	12e5e        56b2        MOV             L,#0B2H // Timer start trigger register
	12e60        7192        SET1            [HL].1H
	12e62        cfbe0100    MOV             !TOM0L,#0H // Timer output mode register
	12e66        716b21      CLR1            PM1.6H // This is buzzer output
	12e69        c2          POP             BC
	12e6a        d7          RET
